In this video, we cover Intel's presence at CES 2026 -- the Consumer Electronics Show -- and its series of disappointing announcements. Intel sort of mentioned a handheld gaming device, re-announced its Panther Lake silicon, announced a new B390 Arc GPU for mobile, didn't announce a B770 desktop GPU, and then spent the rest of the time spewing AI nonsense.
